@host = https://localhost:7083

### Log in as the admin (engineering department, premium tier)
# @name adminLogin
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

### Log in as the manager (operations department, standard tier)
# @name managerLogin
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manager@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "Manager123!"
}

### Log in as the regular user (no department, free tier)
# @name userLogin
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "User123!"
}

### Inspect your own claims - run this with each token and compare
GET {{host}}/api/me
Authorization: Bearer {{adminLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### Exports - requires a department claim, ANY value (admin: 200, manager: 200)
GET {{host}}/api/exports
Authorization: Bearer {{managerLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### Exports as the regular user - 403 (no department claim at all)
GET {{host}}/api/exports
Authorization: Bearer {{userLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### Deployments - department must equal "engineering" (admin: 200)
GET {{host}}/api/deployments
Authorization: Bearer {{adminLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### Deployments as manager - 403 (operations != engineering)
GET {{host}}/api/deployments
Authorization: Bearer {{managerLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### Premium report - subscription claim added by claims TRANSFORMATION, not the token (admin: 200)
GET {{host}}/api/reports/premium
Authorization: Bearer {{adminLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### Premium report as manager - 403 (standard tier)
GET {{host}}/api/reports/premium
Authorization: Bearer {{managerLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### Workspace - same endpoint, response branches on claims
GET {{host}}/api/workspace
Authorization: Bearer {{userLogin.response.body.$.token}}

### No token at all - 401 Unauthorized
GET {{host}}/api/me